Afghanistan celebrates first medal | Beijing 2008 | Sports | The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata)
                                                                                                                                                                                                             Afghanistan celebrates first medal
                      
	Kabul: The winner of Afghanistans first Olympic medal is to be given a house as a reward on the orders of President Hamid Karzai, a palace official said on Thursday.         
	Rohullah Nikpai thrilled Afghans with his bronze medal in the mens 58kg taekwondo. Its a time of big celebrations for all of us, said shopkeeper Khair Mohammad. Im so happy that despite the war, lack of sports facilities and training Nikpai managed to secure a medal. Many Afghans were unable to watch the bout live because power is intermittent and access to cable television is restricted. (Reuters)                                                                                                                          
